The conservation union, gathering experts from 181 countries in Bangkok, discussed the escalating extinction crisis and warned of the impact on over one billion lives due to reef destruction.
Human activities, climate change, and introduced species are major factors in reef depletion.
Poverty and population growth exacerbate the situation in South Asia.
The recent tsunamis devastated marine life, with coral reefs taking centuries to recover.
Efforts to protect coral reefs include artificial reef creation and removal of harmful debris.
Urgent action is needed to prevent further damage and preserve these vital ecosystems.
